 Law]]\n[[Category:Eldest sons of barons]]\n[[Category:Chairmen of the Conservative Party (UK)]]\n[[Category:Conservative Party (UK) life peers]]\n[[Category:Peers nominated by David Cameron]]\n[[Category:Conservative Party (UK) MPs for English constituencies]]\n[[Category:Councillors in the City of Westminster]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Members of the Privy Council of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:People educated at Abingdon School]]\n[[Category:People from Abingdon-on-Thames]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1983\u20131987]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1987\u20131992]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1997\u20132001]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 2001\u20132005]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 2005\u20132010]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 2010\u20132015]]\n[[Category:Governors of Abingdon School]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the English recipient of the Victoria Cross|Francis Cornwallis Maude}}\n{{Short description|British Conservative politician}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n|honorific-prefix = [[The Right Honourable]]\n|name             = The Lord Maude of Horsham\n|honorific-suffix = {{post-nominals|country=GBR|size=100%|PC}}\n|image            = Francis Maude, Minister for the Cabinet Office.jpg\n|office           = [[Minister of State for Trade|Minister of State for Trade and Investment]]\n|primeminister    = [[David Cameron]]\n|term_start       = 11 May 2015\n|term_end         = 10 February 2016\n|predecessor      = [[Ian Livingston, Baron Livingston of Parkhead|The Lord Livingston of Parkhead]]\n|successor        = [[Mark Price, Baron Price|The Lord Price]]\n|office1          = [[Minister for the Cabinet Office]]<br>[[Paymaster General]]\n|primeminister1   = [[David Cameron]]\n|term_start1      = 12 May 2010\n|term_end1        = 11 May 2015\n|predecessor1     = [[Tessa Jowell]]\n|successor1       = [[Matthew Hancock|Matt Hancock]]\n|office2          = [[Chairman of the Conservative Party]]\n|leader2          = [[Michael Howard]]<br>[