 Don}}\n[[Category:1937 births]]\n[[Category:Canadian academics]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Sarnia]]\n[[Category:Writers from Ontario]]\n[[Category:Canadian non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:Canadian male novelists]]\n[[Category:Canadian mystery writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Canadian novelists]]\n[[Category:20th-century Canadian poets]]\n[[Category:Canadian male poets]]\n[[Category:21st-century Canadian novelists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Canadian poets]]\n[[Category:University of Western Ontario faculty]]\n[[Category:20th-century Canadian male writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Canadian male writers]]\n[[Category:Canadian male non-fiction writers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2013}}\n{{multiple issues|\n{{notability|date=December 2017}}\n{{COI|date=December 2017}}\n}}\n'''Donald George Gutteridge''' (born 30 September 1937) is a Canadian author of poetry, fiction and scholarly works. He is also professor emeritus at the [[University of Western Ontario]].\n\n== Biography ==\n\nDon Gutteridge was born in [[Sarnia]], [[Ontario]] in 1937, and was raised in the nearby village of [[Point Edward, Ontario]]. His high schooling took place in [[Sarnia]] and [[Chatham, Ontario]]. He attended the [[University of Western Ontario]] (UWO), where he graduated with a [[Bachelor of Arts|BA Honours]] in English in 1960. After graduating, Gutteridge taught high school English for seven years before joining the Faculty of Education at UWO in 1969.  He is currently Professor Emeritus. In 1970 he won the UWO President's Medal for his poem \"Death at Quebec.\" Poet John B. Lee, winner of 50 poetry prizes, called Gutteridge a \"major poet.\" \"<ref name=New>{{cite book|last=New|first=William H.|title=Encyclopedia of Literature in Canada|year=2002|publisher=University of Toronto Press|location=Toronto|isbn=9780802007612|pages=462\u20133|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Mkh2vJ_9GpEC&pg=PA462&dq=encyclopedia+literature+canada+don+gutteridge+sarnia+ON+Grace&hl=en&sa=X&ei=0v8FUKiHMovxsgahjYHxBg&ved=0CDQQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=encyclopedia%20literature%20canada%20don%20gutteridge%20sarnia%20ON%20Grace&f=false}}</ref><ref name=Benson>{{cite book|last=Benson|first=Eugene|title=The Oxford Companion to Canadian Literature|year=1997|publisher=Oxford University Press|location=Toronto|isbn=978-0195411676|pages=[https://archive.org/details/oxfordcompaniont00toye/page/505 505\u20136]|edition=2nd|author2=William Toye|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/oxfordcompaniont00toye/page/505}}</ref><ref name=Power>{{cite web|last=Power|first=Alana|title=Turncoat by Don Gutteridge|url=http://www.thelondoner.ca/ArticleDisplay.aspx?e=2778412|accessdate=14 July 2012|date=29 September 2010}}</ref><ref name=OpenBook>{{cite web|last=Anon|title=The Proust Questionnaire, with Don Gutteridge|url=http://www.openbookontario.com/news/proust_questionnaire_with_don_gutteridge|publisher=Open Book Ontario|accessdate=14 July 2012|date=18 February 2011}}</ref><ref name=WUC>{{cite web|last=Gutteridge|first=Don|title=Member Profile|url=http://www.writersunion.ca/member/don-gutteridge|work=The Writers' Union of Canada|accessdate=14 July 2012}}</ref><ref name=Colombo>{{cite book|last=Colombo|first=John Robert|title=Canadian Literary Landmarks|year=1984|publisher=Dundurn Press|isbn=9780888820730|pages=135|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0zbdUkJkm10C&pg=PA135&lpg=PA135&dq=don+gutteridge+award+poetry&source=bl&ots=JeAhlYRWor&sig=N40kn5HePnEewji21lB3thNUPgQ&hl=en&sa=X&ei=7EQDUJaXDY6U0QWU79D_Bg&ved=0CFEQ6AEwAjge#v=onepage&q=don%20gutteridge%20award%20poetry&f=false}}</ref>\nOne reviewer, Jack Magnus, said Gutteridge _has a divine gift <https://www.goodreads.com/author/list/192009.Don_Gutteridge>\nHe lives in [[London, Ontario]] He has two children, John and Kate, and six grandchildren.<ref name=WUC />\n\n==Published works==\n===Poetry===\n\n* ''Riel: A Poem For Voices''. Fiddlehead Poetry Books: Fredericton, 1968; and Van Nostrand Reinhold: Toronto, 1972.\n* ''The Village Within''. Fiddlehead: Fredericton, 1970.\n* ''Death At Quebec and Other Poems''. Fiddlehead: Fredericton, 1971.\n* \"Perspectives: Poems Toward a Biography.\" Pennywise Press, London, Ontario, 1971.\n* ''Saying Grace: An Elegy''. Fiddlehead: Fredericton, 1972.\n* ''Coppermine: The Quest For North''. Oberon: Ottawa, 1973.\n* ''Borderlands''. Oberon: Ottawa, 1975.\n* ''Tecumseh''. Oberon: Ottawa, 1976.\n* ''A True History of Lambton County''. Oberon: Ottawa, 1977.\n* ''God\u2019s Geography''. Brick Books: London, 1982.\n* ''The Exiled Heart; Selected Narratives''.  Oberon: Ottawa, 1986.\n* ''Love in the Wintertime''. Oberon: Ottawa, 1990.\n* ''Flute Music in the Cello\u2019s Belly''. Moonstone: Goderich, 1997.\n* ''Bloodlines''. Oberon: Ottawa, 2001.\n* ''Something More Miraculous''. Oberon: Ottawa, 2004.\n* ''Still Magical''. Oberon: Ottawa, 2007.\n* ''Coming Home''. Oberon: Ottawa, 2011.\n* ''The Way It Was''. Friesen Press: Vancouver, 2014.\n* ''Tidings''. Black Moss Press: Windsor, 2015.\n* ''Peripheries''. (ebook) First Choice Books: Victoria, 2016.\n* ''Inundations''. Hidden Brook Press: Brighton, 2016.\n* ''The Blue Flow Below''. Black Moss Press: Windsor, 2017.\n* \"The Sands of Canatara \" (ebook) First Choice Books: Victoria, 2017.\n* \"Inklings\" Black Moss Press: Windsor, 2017.\n* \"The Village Within\" (re-issue, ebook)) First Choice Books: Victoria, 2017.\n* \"Cameron Lake\" (ebook) First Choice Books: Victoria, 2018.\n* \"Home Ground\" Hidden Brook Press, 2018.\n* \"Two Dozen for Anne, First Choice books, Victoria, 2018\n* \"Bereft: Poems for my Beloved,\" First Choice Books, Victoria, 2018.\n* \"Another Poem For Anne,\" First Choice Books, Victoria, 2018.\n* \"Days Worth the Telling,\" Black Moss Press, Windsor, 2018.\n* \"The Breath of My Being,\" First Choice Books, Victoria, 2018.\n* \"Foster's Pond,\" Borealis, Ottawa, 2019\n* \"The Star-Brushed Horizon,' Hidden Brook Press, 2019.\n* \"Mara's Lamp,\" Bl